RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (QUARTER HORSE RACE 1 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 53. Maiden Claiming Purse 9500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ASPHALT ANDY stalked pace two wide on the backstretch, continued two wide on the turn, advanced three wide late on the turn, took aim and powered away when asked, in a convincing win. CAPACITY stalked pace along the inside, continued to be along the inside on the turn, swung aggressively five wide into the lane, kept to task in the lane to get up for second. REAL THIRSTY went to rail as rivals stayed wide on the backstretch, had to ride cautiously into the turn when rivals came over, had to steady off heels mid turn, regathered and tried to ease out and had to steady again when lacking room due to ASPHALT ANDY beating him to the spot, altered inside in upper stretch and earned third along the rail. GOTHAM'S FINALE vied three wide on the backstretch, continued three wide on the turn, entered lane in mix, kept on gamely till faltering late. POCO DIABLO ROJO away best, kept in the six path and vied for lead along with outside rival, angled to rail entering the turn, continued to vie for lead on the turn, entered lane in the lead and kept trying till weakening in the final sixteenth. ACCELERAY away cleanly, climbed early and dropped back, settled well off the pace and showed mild interest late. FEVER away well, settled off the pace near the rail, continued near rail on the turn and failed to produce a rally. LORD MO settled off the pace three wide on the backstretch, continued three wide on the turn and failed to threaten.

ENTRY.NAME: Acceleray
ENTRY.OWNER: Gans Doug Jacobs Gary Katz Larry Riggs Kevin and Wright Robert

ENTRY.NAME: Real Thirsty
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased inside, off heels turn, lacked room 1/8, altered in,up 3rd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (QUARTER HORSE RACE 2 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 70. Claiming Purse 8500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since September 18 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200 (Maiden Races And Races For $2,500 Or Less Not Con sidered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROCK N ROLL SONG tracked duo two wide on the backstretch, continued off the duel three wide on the turn, ranged up on dueling pair entering the lane, and easily drove past. PETE'S INFERNO failed to keep up early, had to drop back and settled of the pace, advanced on the turn two wide, launched bid three wide and finished willingly. RUN AUNTIE T RUN dueled along the inside on the backstretch, continued to hold the rail on the turn, entered lane in a three horse battle, proved no match for the winner, but outfinished dueling rival for show. NENE ROMANO dueled two wide on the backstretch, continued two wide on the turn, entered lane in between and outfinished by rivals in the lane. QUIET FOREST stalked duo along the inside on the backstretch, continued to track duo on the turn and failed to threaten in the lane. HAMPTONRUN hopped and came away very slow, not persevered with throughout and never threatened.

ENTRY.NAME: Quiet Forest
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked duo inside, needed more inside

ENTRY.NAME: Rock N Roll Song
ENTRY.OWNER: Moreno Jr Ariel Avillalobos and Moreno Ariel
